command : git 
This helps to know the complete detail

command : git -v
Helps to know the version

Setting the user name and emal

$ git config --global user.name "Sumeet"
$ git config --global user.email "sumeetjoshi568@gmail.com"

$ git config --list


staging area : It is the place where we can preview our commit

$ git status
This command helps us to know weather the file is repository or no

$ git init
Initialise the folder to git by creating the repository


$ git add .
this will push all the files to the staging area of the git

$ git add index.html
this will push particular file to the staging area

$ git commit -m "Initial commit"
This we made the our files to go to the repository

$ git log
commit 7802691c04c4aadc724be79cb9e9579db74521a0 (HEAD -> master)
Author: Sumeet <sumeetjoshi568@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Apr 4 18:44:49 2026 +0530

    Initial commit
[Here we get to see the commit we are able to make]

-----------------------------------------------

Note: You do the changes in the any of the file and you make 
$ git status
 modified:   index.html
 modified:   notes.txt

we get to know which all files are modified

-----------------------------------------------

To know all the commits in the one line
$ git log --oneline

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To clone any one's project from the GitHub we can do that by git clone method

$ git clone project's URL link from GitHub

we get the project's URL link from the GitHub repository 

Note: To paste anything on the Gitbash use 'shift + insert'

Note that always do not run the git init in the cloned projects
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
To get the branch name 
$ git branch

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Note very important and trick

If somewhere 'git bash; get hangs or nothing gets work
in the directory there is hidden folder called as '.git'
in that folder there will be file named as 'index lock' just manually delete that
then again the 'git bash'  will start to work normally
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

$ git diff 
It is the command tell us that 
in which files what modification we made 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To revert back any changes we made use
$ git restore file_name

To restore all the file
$ git restore .
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To restore the file from the staged
$ git restore --staged file_name
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To amend the previous commit or to change the previous commit use
$ git commit --amend -m "Commit_message"

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Some data we don't want to be associated with the public repository 
that is where we use git ignore

to push more files into git ignore mode 
in the git ignore file write
*.extension_of_file
eg *.py, *.txt

if situation arrives only single or two files has to be pushed
the in the git igore file write it as 
!filename.ext


to pus the folder into git ignore
in the git ignore write file_name/
